
To find out which character map is in use type in the command 

 $ **locale charmap**
 $ **locale -a** lists all the maps on the system

To create new locals put it into **/etc/locale.gen** (posted by Kai
Groﬂjohann):

<example>

 de_DE.UTF-8 UTF-8
 en_GB.UTF-8 UTF-8
 en_US.UTF-8 UTF-8

</example>

See also *localedef* and localegen (debian)
